com.ibm.ecm.api.coresdk.factory

Class IBMECMFactory

  • Object
    • IBMECMFactory

  • public class IBMECMFactory
extends Object
    A singleton factory that provides entry points to the top-level API objects, such as IBMECMApplication or IBMECMDesktop.

    Most of the time you will start with the following: 

    IBMECMApplication application = IBMECMFactory.getInstance.getApplication(baseURL)

      • overrideSettings

        public boolean overrideSettings(Map<String,Long> settings)
        Optional method that must be called before any applications are created. Calling this will override the default values for any of the SDK parameters supplied. Setting unknown values will have no effect on the SDK. Additional calls of this method after the first call will be ignored. (false will be returned) Calls to this method after the first getApplication is called will be ignored. (false will be returned) Allows the setting of the following SDK wide parameters: [Default value shown in ()'s]

        repository.cache.max.size (100) - Maximum number of repository objects to cache before objects get pushed out by LRU algorithm.

        repository.cache.timeout.ms (-1 infinite) - Timeout value for repository objects system wide

        item.property.cache.max.size (2000) - Max number of property objects that can be shared in the global item property cache.

        item.property.cache.timeout.ms (-1 infinite) - Timeout value for shared global item property cache.

        http.client.timeout.connect.seconds (30) - HTTP connect timeout.

        http.client.timeout.write.seconds (30) - HTTP write timeout.

        http.client.timeout.read.seconds (30) - HTTP read timeout.

        Parameters:
        settings - A map of override keys and values
        Returns:
        True if the settings have been accepted. (if this call is made before all others)

      • getCurrentApplication

        public IBMECMApplication getCurrentApplication()
        Returns a reference to the current application if it exists. If no applications have been set yet, this will return null. The current application will be the one that was created with the most recent call to getApplication. As a result it is important be aware that the value returned here may not always be the same depending on if there have been subsequent calls to getApplication.
        Returns:
        the current IBMECMApplication

      • getApplication

        public IBMECMApplication getApplication(String baseURL)
        Returns an instance of IBMECMApplication based on the IBM Content Navigator URL that is passed in. A word about acceptSelfSignedCertificates: Setting this parameter to true results in a Application object that will accept any certificate. This is a large security concern and it is not recommended to be used in production environments.

        Caching and getCurrentApplication : Calling this method where the combination of baseURL and acceptSelfSignedCertificates are the same as the current application (see getCurrentApplication) will result in a reference to the current application, not the creation of a new one. Only passing values for these parameters that are different from the current application will result in a new application object being created.

        acceptSelfSignedCertificates defaults to false if not provided.

        Parameters:
        baseURL - the IBM Content Navigator URL. Syntax: http[s]://<server>:<port>/navigator/[?desktop=<desktopname>]
        Returns:
        an instance of IBMECMApplication

      • getApplication

        public IBMECMApplication getApplication(String baseURL,
                                        IBMECMAuthenticatorDataSource authenticatorDataSource,
                                        boolean acceptSelfSignedCertificates)
        Returns an instance of IBMECMApplication based on the IBM Content Navigator URL that is passed in. Use this method to provide a data source for custom authentication use cases. A word about acceptSelfSignedCertificates: Setting this parameter to true results in a Application object that will accept any certificate. This is a large security concern and it is not recommended to be used in production environments.
        Parameters:
        baseURL - the IBM Content Navigator URL. Syntax: http[s]://<server>:<port>/navigator/[?desktop=<desktopname>]
        authenticatorDataSource - the authenticator data source that enables custom authentication to be injected
        acceptSelfSignedCertificates - true if you want to accept all certificates (note this is not secure and is for testing only)
        Returns:
        an instance of IBMECMApplication
